5) Estimating size of the cluster
	eg:
   cluster capacity =   ( 3 times of actual size of data ) + 40%*( 3 times of actual size of data )
   machine configurations 

	1)two NameNodes ( ANN and PNN )
	Storage Heavy Configuration (2U/machine): 
	Two hex-core CPUs, 
	48GB memory,
	2 disk drives ( each 2TB). 

	2) SecondaryNameNode (optional )
	Storage Heavy Configuration (2U/machine): 
	Two hex-core CPUs, 
	48GB memory,
	2 disk drives ( each 2TB). 


  	3)Two Resource Managers ( ARM, PRM )
	Storage Heavy Configuration (2U/machine): 
	Two hex-core CPUs, 
	48GB memory,
	2 disk drives ( each 2TB).

	4) Edit  logs 
	lowend system ( basic configuration )
	one hex-core CPUs, 
	4GB memory,
	1 disk drive of 1TB

	5) Data nodes
	1)Two hex-core CPUs,
	2)16GB 
	3)12 disk drives (2TB )directly attached using the motherboard controller as twins with 	two motherboards and 12 drives in a single cabinet.
          total capacity 24TB

	actual size of data  = 10 pb
	 size in TB  = 10*1024 = 10240 TB
	estimated total size = (10240 + 0.4 * 10240 ) * 3 = 43008
	nodes = 43008 TB  /24 TB = 1792 (around 1800 nodes )
 
